{
  "text": "Independently of Cdk2/Cdk4 activation, E2 reduces Cdkinhibiting proteins like p27 and p21 by the induction of proteasomal degradation [CITATION_1] ). Among other targets, it activates the Ras-Erk pathway by binding AF-1 and AF-2 to the p160 component of the coactivator complex recruited by Jun/Fos and so activating the coactivator [CITATION_2] .",
  "correct_citation": {
